CREATE TABLE products (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name_es TEXT,
    name_en TEXT,
    description_es TEXT,
    description_en TEXT,
    category_es TEXT,
    category_en TEXT
);
Advantage: simple to manage if your dataset isnâ€™t huge.

Search: you can build a tsvector that combines both languages.

sql
Copy code
SELECT *
FROM products
WHERE to_tsvector('spanish', name_es || ' ' || description_es || ' ' || category_es)
      || to_tsvector('english', name_en || ' ' || description_en || ' ' || category_en)
      @@ plainto_tsquery('spanish', 'queso') 
      OR plainto_tsquery('english', 'cheese');
NORMALIZE THE ABOVE